Sheila Dabney https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sheila_Dabney 0 Sheila Dabney is an African-American actor, best known for her co-starring role in the 1987 lesbian feminist film She Must Be Seeing Things alongside Lois Weaver and directed by Sheila McLaughlin.In 1984, Dabney won an Obie Award for her performance as Sarita in Maria Irene Fornés' play Sarita.
